Try Wild Alaskan caught scallops from the Kodiak area. They tend to be larger, firmer, and low in mercury and other "undesirables." Alaskan Halibut cheeks are also a really good cheaper alternative. I doubled the garlic and herbs and thought it was a recipe worth repeating.

